Abastab (2008)

Director: Kamalesh Maitra
Producr: Sudip Kanjilal
Music Director: Chandan Roychowdhury
Genre: Drama
Cast:  Rituparna Sengupta, Abhishek, Subhashis
Playback: Kabir Suman, Rupankar, Anushua, Enakkhi


The story explores the social problems faced by the ordinary/slum dwelling people of the country who work very hard just in order to survive. One side there's a jobless youth belonging to a poor household. The father, the sole earner, always grumbling at the lack of ambitiousness in his sons whiles the mother protecting his sons from his wrathful eyes and ever sharp tongue. The other side we find a widow single mother working day and night doing petty tailoring for her daughter's good future and eventually getting exploited by her master, in exchange of some money to fend for her family's needs ends up committing suicide. An ailing man dying in a street full of passersby who are all too busy to even spare a glance and a thought, show a bit of humanity and take him to the hospital for help. The city stops for nobody but how thousands are falling prey to the lecherous society is what the story is all about.


